OL,3,CWoman's fury after 'corridor care'
OL,4,Cnightmare at hospital
OL,6,F"Being in that corridor was not the
OL,7,Fplace for him to be at all."
OL,9,F"It's obvious they just can't cope
OL,10,Fwith the amount of people that are
OL,11,Fgoing through the William Harvey
OL,12,FHospital A&E and it's not the staff's
OL,13,Ffault, it's a management problem and a
OL,14,Fcapacity problem.
OL,16,FOn the second night in the corridor,
OL,17,Fwhile Janet was sleeping, Nick
OL,18,Fdisappeared.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/13
