OL,4,Cnightmare at hospital
OL,6,F"We are very sorry to anyone who has
OL,7,Fwaited or been cared for in a
OL,8,Fcorridor. This is not the standard of
OL,9,Fcare or experience we want for any of
OL,10,Four patients, and we are continuing to
OL,11,Ftake steps to reduce waiting times and
OL,12,Fprevent corridor care wherever
OL,13,Fpossible."
OL,15,FAccording to the charity, Age UK, so
OL,16,Fcalled 'corridor care' is becoming
OL,17,F'normal' in hospitals with some even
OL,18,Fadvertising for corridor care staff.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@JO]
